@startuml
title OciQueue Formal Lifecycle

[*] --> Observed
Observed --> Retryable : CREATING, UPDATING
Observed --> Active : ACTIVE
Observed --> Failed : FAILED, DELETED
Active --> Active : supported drift update\n(displayName, visibility, timeout,\nDLQ count, tags, custom key)
Active --> DeletePending : delete requested
Retryable --> DeletePending : delete requested
Failed --> DeletePending : delete requested
DeletePending --> Deleted : finalizer removed after delete

state Retryable
state Active
state Failed
state DeletePending
state Deleted

note right of Active
  retentionInSeconds drift is rejected
  before any compartment move or UpdateQueue call.
  Empty customEncryptionKeyId is a no-op.
end note
@enduml
